# 2p_kill — multi-round kill test.
#
# The host owns authoritative positions, so it teleports BOTH
# mechs to their layout positions (the client's spawn_at is just
# cosmetic until snapshots arrive). Both end up adjacent on the
# ground with no terrain between them.
#
# Round 1: host fires Pulse Rifle right at the client → kill.
# Summary 4 s (countdown sync verified).
# Round 2: roles reverse — client fires left at host → kill.
#
# Exercises: kill flow over the wire, round transitions, summary
# countdown sync, respawn at peer_spawn point each round.

window 1280 720
out build/shots/net/kill_host
network host 24091
name HostA
loadout - "Pulse Rifle" - Light Standard

# Host (slot 0) spawns at world (1300, 1112). Client (slot 1)
# spawns at (1500, 1112). 200 px gap, both on the ground in a
# clear area (left of the col-55 wall).
spawn_at 1300 1112
peer_spawn 1 1500 1112

# ---- Round 1: host fires right at client ----
# Match starts ~tick 130. Aim at client's chest (1500, 1080) so
# hitscan rays land on torso bones.
at 150 aim 1500 1080
at 160 press fire
at 700 release fire

# ---- Round 2: host stays put, client kills it ----
# Just sit there.

# ---- Screenshots ----------------------------------------------------
at 170  shot r1_match_start
at 250  shot r1_firing
at 360  shot r1_kill
at 700  shot r1_summary
at 870  shot r2_lobby
at 1000 shot r2_match_start
at 1200 shot r2_dying
at 1400 shot r2_summary
at 1500 end

contact_sheet sheet cols 3 cell 320 180
